{"/service/ndnp/in/batch_in_janeway_ver01/data/sn87055779/00416150886/1930103101/0359.xml":{"full_text":"I\nl\n\nPREDICTS HEAVY\nAIRPLANE SALES\nFOR FALL SEASON\nCorporation Announces\nUnusual Record\nFor October.\nDETROIT, Mich., Oct. 30.\u2014Indioa\ntions that the alrcra.lt industry' wlB\nhave an unusually good fall sales sea\nson are seen in the report of the De\ntroit Aircraft corporation, announcing\nsales of 15 airplanes having a gross\nvalue of $104,050 for the 10-day period\nfrom Oct. 1 to 10.\nThis total is 11 percent above the\nprevious 10-day period for sales of\nthe company which occurred In Sep\ntember of this year. No comparative\nfigures are available for 1930.\nSales Included three Lockheeds, two\nEastman Amphibians, an Eastman\nFlying Yacht, four Parks training\nplanes, two Ryan cabin planes, a Ryan\nSpeedster and a Blackburn Bluebird.\nDeliveries of 10 planes having a gross\nvalue of $81,000 for which orders had\nbeen placed previously were made in\nthe same period.\nIndividuals Boy\n'Tew airplanes are bought by cor\nporations, individuals and commercial\noperators when the business outlook\nfor the future is bad,\u201d Karl S. Betts,\nacting general sales manager, stated\nIn making the announcement, \"and\nso we believe that the sale of 48 air\nplanes that we have made in the last\nthree months to such people, indi\ncate that business Is expected to be\nbetter in the next few months than\nthe usual business Indicators would\nshow.\n\"Purchasers are becoming more dis\ncriminating than was the case in\n1929, taking plenty of time to find the\nbest possible value in the ship best\nfitted to their needs.\n\"We do not believe that price re\nductions result in greatly Increased\nsales totals, and the Detroit Aircraft\ncorporation has consistently refused to\nenter in to price cutting competition\nthat has been current in the industry\nin recent months.\nExports Revive\n\"It is interesting to note that export\nbusiness in the aircraft industry shows\nsigns of a heavy revival, the Detroit\nAircraft corporation having received\ngross orders totalling over $50,000 for\nshipment to foreign countries to the\nlast 30 days. We believe that export\nsales will play a large part in keeping\nAmerican aircraft production near\npresent levels during the winter\nmonths.\u201d\n7*\nCLIENTS ARE GIVEN\n\u2018PROFESSIONAL\u2019 RANK\nBy International \\ewi Service:\nPARIS, Oct. 30.\u2014The hand-writing\non the wall system has been adopted\nrecently by certain French peddlers.\nLike numerous beggars, they work in\nchains. Each has a district and\nleaves signs for his fellows who fol\nlow after him.\nA zero chalked on the garden gate,\nthe doorstep or lamp-post nearby,\nmeans that there is nothing doing\nat this house and it is better to pass\nit by.\nSeveral dots mean go ahead, smooth\nsailing and usually good luck.\nAn exclamation point suggests:\nOffer only your best stuff for the cus\ntomer knows how to Judge it.\nA little square means: Don't hesi\ntate, urge a little.\nA star means: If mistress not in,\ncome back.\nLAKE TRANSPARENCY STUDIED\nBy I'nttrd Press:\nMADISON, Wis.\u2014Study of trans\nparency of Wisconsin lakes by use of\nthe Pyrlimnometer, or sun machine,\nis one of the tasks of 79-year-oid Dr.\nEdward A. Birge, president emeritus\nof the University of Wisconsin. Dr.\nBirge has returned from northern\nWisconsin where he analyzed lake\ntransparency and the effect it has on\nfish life, aquatic vegetation, and the\nchemical content of lake water.\nHIGH LIGHTS OF HISTORY\n27. Daniel Bdone\u2014A Sacrifice That Saved Boonesborou\nBy J. CARROLL MANSFIELD\nQ^kfflJOeP 9* A LMMe WAR PASTY OPjkAW\num5 UNpftR Chief Buck Pish, Boone was\nWSMAYftp TO HEARTHET MIS CAPWRS WERE\nOMTHE WAY Tb ATTACK 0OONES0OQOUEN.\nDooms knew thatwctn most op the mew *hw\nTHE PORT &OOLt> HOT HQ1E> OUT.\nI SAME THE WOMEN ANt> CHILDREN LETT\nALMOST pEFewSELESS AT BOONESBOROUGM,\nBoone resolved To sacrifice his uttle BN*ry\nat Blue Jj ch Me tolp Black Fi sh that the fort\nWAS TOO STRONG To BETAKEN AMO SUEOeSTEp\nTHAT, INSTEAD, HC SURPRISE THE MEN AT THE LICK\n\u00aeOOWfe SUGGESTION PLEA960 BUCK FlSM,\nANO HE AT ONCE LEO HIS B&W&S TOWARD\nBlue Lick. Engrossed in making salt\nAND NOT EXPECTING AN ATTACK, BOONE'S\nCOMRAOeS AT THE LlCK WERE EASILY SUR\nPRISED ANP QUICKLY MAPft PRISONERS.\nBY MIS CAPTURaS/BUCK FlfH\nGAME UP TUB IDEA OP ATTACHING\nBoonesborou gm ANp starter for\nhoms.Aftbr MORE than A V\u00abKi march\nTHE PARTY REACHED THE CHW VttlABF\nOF THE SHAWNEES.\nK\nEX-KING FREDERICK\nHAS VEIN OF HUMOR\nBy International Bow* Serried\nBERLIN, Oct. 30.\u2014Ex-King Fred\nerick: August of Saxony recently met\none of his former government offi\ncials who Inquired after the king\u2019s\nhealth. \"Thanks, I\u2019m quite well,\u201d\nFrederick replied, \"but look at my\nformer colleagues. They are much\nworse off: they are either dead or\nthey re-married.\"\nFTOMATO JUICE^t\nCOCKTAIL\nTo four ounces of tomofo\njuice use one teaspoon of\nLEA\nPERRINS\nSAUCE\nHOW TO APPEAR TALL AND SLIM\nTHOUGH SHORT AND STOCKT.\nHow to appear tall and slim, al\nthough short and stocky, is not an\neasy problem, and it can not always\nbe done successfully, but in most\ncases, the resulting effect is worth the\nattempt. Certainly, it is better than\nthe Incongruous effect resulting from\nclothes that emphasise the wrong\nlines.\nBriefly and simply, the problem is\nthis: to accent the vertical as much\nas possible. Obviously, a single\nbreasted jacket has more verticals\nthan a double-breasted one and,\ntherefore, should be the choice of the\nshort, stocky man. The jacket should\nbe worn open. The lapels should be\nsoft and rolled the length of the\nfront of the coat, further enhancing\nthe proper effect. Likewise, the waist\ncoat should be single-breasted, with\nvery definite, rather sharp points.\nThis does not mean, of course,\nthat a double-breasted jacket la en\ntirely out of the question for. If It is\nproperly cut, the right effect can be\nachieved. Thla will be discussed hi\nanother article.\nMaterials should be rather\u2019 hard\nand with a smooth finish, for these\ntake a better crease than the softer,\nwooller ones. Likewise, the colors\nsnould be dark.\n(Copyright, 1830, by Vanity Pair)\n\u201cMONOCLE THIEF\u201d TAKEN\nLONDON.\u2014Betrayed by his custom\nof wearing a monocle, H. D. Trevor\nwas arrested after six months\u2019 search\nfor jewel thefts totaling $62,000.\np\n\nJ\n4\nFASTER\nTRAINS\nfrom CHICAGO\nON THE SOUTH SHORE LINE\nTEN MINUTES cat from the naming time of\nthe 7, 9 and 11 o'clock limited trains leaving\nChicago for South Bend. Now go between Chicago and\nSouth Bend in two hoars and twenty minutes or better.\nTranscontinental hurray is combined with outstand.\ning speed to giro South Bend patrons the finest'\nof interarban service in the Sooth Shore line. Dining\nand parlor-car limited* leave South Bend at *7 AiL,\n12 Noon, and 5 FJL daily. Luxurious parlor car\nlimiteds at 10 in the morning and 3 in the afternoon.\nSimilar de luxe service retaining.\nAll trains leaYe from Michigan and La Salle station,\nstopping in Chicago at Kensington, 63rd St. (Wood\nlawn), 53rd St. (Hyde Park), Roosevelt R<L, Van\nBoren St* and Randolph St. L C. suburban stations\non Chicago's Michigan Boulevard.\n1 *Estra fas*\u2014Arrives\nChicago 8:57 AJL\nPhone Ticket Agent, 3-3111,\nfar all information, t\nm\nt\\' --v\nm.\nRAILROAD\nijirour\nCHICAGO SOUTH SHORE AND SOUTH BEND\nr\n;V- i\nV v -f' v\nV v.'--\nV\nStroke of Genius\"\nii;t:\n,sf\n1\n\nGEORG\u00ae S*\npark\u00ae*1\nPen Comp0\u00ae*\njs-c-*\nAbout\nxogkv strike s\nUltra VloU* Ray\nfor product* \u00aef f*\u00ae\n\u00abPeoi.\u00abef g\"LsfetHteneed\u00ab.ery\nderail HU\nbn**1**** toad# to\nt*\"* TCSftrier quality hU t\"r\u00b0^\ning tt\u00ab even f^ feed thii great\nnet. You Have reco^ Ultra\nby your ng> of the\n1 n-\u00ab-s\nLUCKY STBI geruMS.\n^roke of tuodem W*\nS'iH?SiSS3\u2019*\u2022\u201d*\"\nx Tocurtwt*rTW'\nonthist***6*\nI\ni X\nV\